# Start Stop Motor Control

Built in CODESYS V3.5 using Ladder Logic.

## Logic

- START = Normally Open contact
- STOP = Normally Closed contact
- MOTOR = Output coil
- MOTOR contact used as a seal-in (holding) contact

## Operation

1. Press START → MOTOR turns ON.
2. Release START → MOTOR remains ON.
3. Press STOP → MOTOR turns OFF.
4. Release STOP → MOTOR remains OFF until START is pressed again.

## Concepts Learned

- NO and NC contacts
- Output coils
- Tags and PLC memory
- Seal-in / Holding / Latching circuits
- Series (AND) and Parallel (OR) logic
